The paper presents lower bounds for graph problems in the CONGEST model, which is a distributed computing model. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper specifically deals with graph problems, so cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph coloring, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper deals with graph problems, which are often studied in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper also mentions all-pairs-shortest-paths, which is a network optimization problem, and therefore cs.NE (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possible sub-category.
